description: I am not a fan of avocados, but my girlfriend loves them. Usually, I order food and avocado is on the side so that I can give them to her. I random came across this plush animal, which was the color of my apartment building, and gave it to her because "she is my better half that makes me smile." About a week after I gave it to her, I came across a yellow piece of foam core and decided to take the plushie out for an adventure. I sat him down on the foam core and snapped it RAW format. I barely had to brighten any colors in Lightroom. Hope you enjoy my avocado as much as she does!

cover_photo.description:
(and execute)

At least, that’s what I wish it said off to the side. It’s been a long time sine I’ve done both of those things – too long.

I’ve spent the last couple months funemployed and figuring out exactly what I want to do. I found a job a long way away from home that fit the bill and tossed in an application the other day but I’m pretty sure that I won’t get it for one reason or another.

Anyways – putting the application together was a lot of fun. It let me dream like I haven’t since I was in university, and getting it all down on paper was pretty liberating.
